---
import SectionHeader from '../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions | Quantum Code Devs"
  description="Terms and conditions for using Quantum Code Devs website and services."
>
  <section>
    <SectionHeader
      eyebrow="Legal"
      title="Terms & Conditions"
      description="These terms govern your use of our website and any professional services provided by Quantum Code Devs."
      descriptionClass="max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-300"
    />
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Last updated: July 16, 2026</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 grid gap-4">
    <article class="glass-card">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Use of Website</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
        You may use this website for lawful purposes only. You agree not to misuse, disrupt, or attempt unauthorized access to systems connected with this website.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="glass-card">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Service Engagements</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
        Project scope, timelines, deliverables, and payment terms are defined in written agreements or proposals. In case of conflict, signed service agreements take precedence over website terms.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="glass-card">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
        Unless otherwise agreed in writing, all pre-existing frameworks, internal tools, and reusable components remain the property of Quantum Code Devs. Client-owned deliverables are transferred according to the governing project agreement.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="glass-card">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Liability</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect or consequential damages resulting from website use. Service liability terms are governed by signed contracts.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="glass-card">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Contact</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-300">
        Questions about these terms can be sent to hello@quantumcodedevs.com.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>
